<HEAD>House Democrats Looking for New Campaign Talent</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: St Germain in 6th and 9th grafs is CQ</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By STEVEN KOMAROW</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MANCHESTER, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Like scouts in major league baseball, a pair of <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Democrats are looking for talent to keep their team winning atop <LOCATION> Capitol </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION>. But figuring out which potential congressional candidates might get a contract from the voters is a tricky task of balancing the facts _ such as money _ with the intangibles, appearance and that `` hungry look.'' Rep. <PERSON> Beryl </PERSON> <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Ark </LOCATION>., chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congressional </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Campaign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, and Rep. <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Synar </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Okla </LOCATION>., the committee's recruiting chairman, met this weekend with potential candidates in <LOCATION> Rhode </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> _ the two targeted congressional districts Democrats say they might take from the In 1988, Democrats in the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> picked up seats despite the big <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> win on the presidential level. `` We out-hustled and we out-recruited the <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> in terms of candidates,'' said <PERSON> Synar </PERSON>. On their first trip of the 1990 cycle, the Democrats' task was n't finding the potential candidates; it was looking for which one was most likely to win. In <LOCATION> Rhode </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> and <PERSON> Synar </PERSON> met with four Democrats interested in trying to unseat freshman Rep. <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Machtley </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-R.I. </LOCATION>, who beat longtime incumbent <ORGANIZATION> Democrat </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fernand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> St </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION>