<HEAD>Movie About Deng Opens, But Audience Seems Unimpressed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The major summer film, a period piece about senior leader <PERSON> Deng </PERSON> <PERSON> Xiaoping </PERSON>, opened Monday in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> and added to the clamor of praise for the man blamed by many Chinese for the recent military crackdown. `` The Baise Uprising'' has as its hero a 25-year-old <PERSON> Deng </PERSON> leading the peasants of remote Baise in southern <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> to victory over Nationalist troops in 1929. The Nationalists ultimately lost a bloody civil war to the communists and retreated to the island province of <LOCATION> Taiwan </LOCATION> in 1949. The movie's opening comes less than two months after the government called in troops to put down a student-led pro-democracy movement, killing hundreds and perhaps thousands of people. Many Chinese say they have lost confidence in the government as a result, and many hold <PERSON> Deng </PERSON> responsible for the killings. `` The Baise Uprising'' fits neatly into the ideological education all Chinese are required to undergo. Most of those who attended the opening day showings at two <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> theaters were organized by their work units, and the movie could be required viewing for many Chinese. It opens nationwide on Aug. 1, the anniversary of the founding of the <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>. Unless Chinese are told to see the movie, many doubtless would not pay the steep admission fee of about 67 cents _ five times the price of most films. In the one-hour, 45-minute film, <PERSON> Deng </PERSON> is portrayed as a confident, level-headed and charismatic leader with all the answers. But the film also shows a human side that one rarely sees in revolutionary-style movies. There are scenes of <PERSON> Deng </PERSON>, an avid bridge player, playing cards and telling a young girl that the strategies involved in playing bridge and c