<HEAD>City Workers Dialing Long-Distance</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST ST. LOUIS, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A city that has trouble paying for trash collection has been billed for hundreds of unauthorized long-distance telephone calls, including many to dial-a-porn services. The cash-starved city's monthly bills average $ 5,000 and include calls to virtually every state, the <LOCATION> Belleville </LOCATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> Ill. </LOCATION> -RRB- News-Democrat reported Sunday. Many phones in the police and maintenance departments logged calls to `` 900'' prefix adult talk lines, the paper said. Treasurer <PERSON> Charlotte </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> said the number of questionable calls in each month's two-inch-thick bill shows the need for an internal auditor. `` After I suggested it to the -LRB- aldermanic -RRB- council two years ago, they cut my staff in half,'' she said. A continuing cash crunch has made it hard for the city to pay salaries and collect garbage in recent months. In a review of bills from March, April and May, the paper found hundreds of dollars worth of calls from <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> and other places were charged to the city either by reversing the charges or by using a city credit card number. Many outgoing calls from City Hall were equally questionable. There were calls to a trivia line that gives callers a chance to win prizes, to the Dunes Hotel in <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION>, and to a pay phone in a <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION> hospital. And there were at least 16 calls from a <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION> number to the beeper of a man convicted on Friday on charges of running a cocaine ring.
