t want the sessions to turn into a littany of complaints. `` You should n't go if you're just going to say, ` We've got gridlock, somebody ought to do something about it,' because we know that,'' <PERSON> Skinner </PERSON> said. `` These are needs and idea sessions.'' The first meeting outside <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> will be held in <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>, on Tuesday, with the focus on rural transportation issues. The last meetings will be in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> on Sept. 11-12 and will deal with drug and alcohol use in the commercial transportation system and federal research and development.
