 `` Twins'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> MCA </ORGANIZATION> Home Video. VHS-Beta, $ 89.95. Rated PG -RRB- Not since <ORGANIZATION> Laurel </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Hardy </PERSON> has such a physically contrasting comedy team come along: <PERSON> Arnold </PERSON> <PERSON> Schwarzenegger </PERSON> and <PERSON> Danny </PERSON> <PERSON> DeVito </PERSON>. `` Twins'' is simply wonderful entertainment. It's silly, improbable, irreverent. <PERSON> Schwarzenegger </PERSON> and <PERSON> DeVito </PERSON> play twin brothers who were separated at birth. No joke. Seems mom was this `` exceptional'' woman who gave her body to a secret biological experiment in creating a superman. Something went wrong, the egg split and a runt turned up as well. As they reunite, search for their mom, dodge a hitman, uncover the truth of their origins and otherwise scheme and hustle their way through the movie, the duo provide enough laughs to fill a Sunday afternoon family viewing. <PERSON> DeVito </PERSON> continues to impress with good comedic work, both in direction and acting. <PERSON> Schwarzenegger </PERSON>, usually a heavy -LRB- in more ways than one -RRB-, is a giggle in a lighter mood. <PERSON> Ivan </PERSON> <PERSON> Reitman </PERSON> directed `` Twins.'' _ By <PERSON> Dolores </PERSON> <PERSON> Barclay </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Editor </ORGANIZATION>.
