<TEXT>
 The business empire of <PERSON> Bjorn </PERSON> <PERSON> Borg </PERSON> is being liquidated and could go bankrupt because the retired tennis star has refused a bid for new working capital, media reports said Monday. <PERSON> Bjorn </PERSON> <PERSON> Borg </PERSON> <PERSON> Enterprises </PERSON> was hit by a cash crisis after <PERSON> Borg </PERSON> refused a $ 4.6 million infusion to cover the expansion in <ORGANIZATION> Bjorn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Borg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Design </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, a fragrance and fashion company, the newspaper <ORGANIZATION> Aftonbladet </ORGANIZATION> and the nationa news agency <ORGANIZATION> TT </ORGANIZATION> said. The financing plan was offered by Swedish financier <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Gyllenhammar </PERSON> and would have allowed <PERSON> Borg </PERSON> to remain the majority owner, the reports said. Further details of the plan were not disclosed. The <PERSON> Bjorn </PERSON> <PERSON> Borg </PERSON> company office in <LOCATION> Stockholm </LOCATION> did not answer the telephone Monday. <ORGANIZATION> Aftonbladet </ORGANIZATION> quoted <PERSON> Borg </PERSON> as saying he would not comment. Business partners quoted by <ORGANIZATION> Aftonbladet </ORGANIZATION> and by <ORGANIZATION> TT </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Borg </PERSON> had given `` no explanation'' for his decision to refuse the financing plan at a board meeting Thursday. Aftonbladet and <ORGANIZATION> TT </ORGANIZATION> said the company board resigned, including <PERSON> Hakan </PERSON> <PERSON> Frisinger </PERSON>, a former managing director of automaker <ORGANIZATION> Volvo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> AB </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Borg </PERSON>'s partner <PERSON> Lars </PERSON> <PERSON> Skarke </PERSON>, who owns a 25 percent share in the group, told <ORGANIZATION> TT </ORGANIZATION> one reason for needing new working capital was brisk sales. <PERSON> Stig </PERSON> <PERSON> Sjoholm </PERSON>, a lawyer and vice president of <ORGANIZATION> Bjorn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Borg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Design </ORGANIZATION> group, told <ORGANIZATION> Aftonbladet </ORGANIZATION> turnover had quadrupled in the past year. `` It is possible our expansion has been too rapid on certain points,'' he said. The Monte Carlo-based <ORGANIZATION> Bjorn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Borg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enterprises </ORGANIZATION> owned companies which designed and marketed a line of quality fashions and fragrances, and was involved in Swedish real estate. <PERSON> Borg </PERSON>, 33, founded his empire on the winnings of a 10-year professional tennis career, including an unmatched five consecutive championships at <LOCATION> Wimbledon </LOCATION>, from 1976 through 1980, and six French Open crowns. By the time he retired from the circuit in 1983, he was estimated to have amassed $ 75 million in prizes and endorsements. He declared his personal wealth in his 1986 tax return as nearly $ 8 million.
