 <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beckman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the pharmaceuticals manufacturer, said Monday its second-quarter earnings rose 20 percent over the same period last year. <PERSON> SmithKline </PERSON> <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON> said net income for the quarter was $ 118.6 million, or 94 cents a share, compared with $ 98.7 million, or 79 cents a share in the second quarter of 1988. The company said sales rose 10 percent to $ 1.26 billion from $ 1.14 billion in the same 1988 quarter. Sales in its clinical laboratory services, consumer health care and eye and skin care divisions showed the largest increases. The stronger <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> dollar compared to other currencies undercut total corporate sales by $ 31 million for the second quarter, the company said. For the first six months of 1989, <PERSON> Smithkline </PERSON> <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON> said earnings dropped 6 percent to $ 248.8 million, or $ 1.99 a share, from $ 265.3 million, or $ 2.13 a share, in the first half of 1988. <PERSON> SmithKline </PERSON> <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON> shareholders are to vote Wednesday on a proposal to merge with <ORGANIZATION> Beecham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> to form <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beecham </ORGANIZATION>. As part of the merger, <ORGANIZATION> Beckman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Instruments </ORGANIZATION> will be spun off as an independent company. <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON>, a supplier of laboratory instruments and consumer products for health care, became partially public in 1988. Currently, 84 percent of <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON> shares are held by <ORGANIZATION> SmithKline </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beckman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Those shares are to be redistributed as part of the recapitalization of <PERSON> SmithKline </PERSON> <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON> if approved at Wednesday's shareholders Quarterly earnings for <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON>, as reported both in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> and at <ORGANIZATION> Beckman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Instruments </ORGANIZATION> headquarters in <LOCATION> Fullerton </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, were $ 11.4 million, or 40 cents per share, down from $ 12.1 million or 42 cents per share last year. <PERSON> Beckman </PERSON> sales were $ 200.5 million, up 3 percent from $ 194.7 million in the second quarter of 1988.
