<HEAD>Cray Says Hitachi Deal Does Not Include Sharing Of Trade Secrets</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TONY KENNEDY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Supercomputer rivals <ORGANIZATION> Cray </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Hitachi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> on Monday confirmed that they have agreed to license their patents to each other freely, but <ORGANIZATION> Cray </ORGANIZATION> said the pact does not allow for joint marketing or sharing of trade secrets. Previous press reports were mistaken in saying the pact would allow the two compaies to share information not yet patented, said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Swenson </PERSON>, a spokesman for Minneapolis-based <ORGANIZATION> Cray </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Hitachi </ORGANIZATION> issued a statement to confirm the existence of the cross-licensing agreement but a spokesman in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> declined further comment. <PERSON> Swenson </PERSON> said such agreements are customary in the computer industry. But he said <ORGANIZATION> Hitachi </ORGANIZATION> is the first Japanese company to sign such an agreement with <ORGANIZATION> Cray </ORGANIZATION>. Convex Computers of <PERSON> Richardson </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, and Supertek Computers of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> have similar agreements with <ORGANIZATION> Cray </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Swenson </PERSON> said. `` The agreement gives each company freedom to pursue designs without having to be concerned about accidental design overlaps involving a patent held by the other company,'' <PERSON> Swenson </PERSON> said. `` If we should stumble onto one another's technology, we've agreed not to litigate.'' The <ORGANIZATION> Kyodo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and the nationally circulated <ORGANIZATION> Asahi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANI