<HEAD>New Orleans Station Sold for $46.8 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Pulitzer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Publishing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to buy <ORGANIZATION> WDSU-TV </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> affiliate in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION>, for $ 46.8 million from <ORGANIZATION> Cosmos </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION>, Pulitzer announced Monday. Pulitzer, a <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis-based </LOCATION> newspaper and broadcast company, said in a news release issued here by WDSU-TV that the sale awaits <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> approval. WDSU-TV, which went on the air in 1948, is <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>'s oldest television station. It was bought by <ORGANIZATION> Cosmos </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> in 1972. The station reported 1988 revenues of $ 16.5 million. Pulitzer's other TV properties are <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> network affiliates KOAT-TV in <LOCATION> Albuquerque </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.M. </LOCATION>, KETV-TV in <LOCATION> Omaha </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Neb. </LOCATION>, WPTA-TV in <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Wayne </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ind. </LOCATION>, and WLKY-TV, <LOCATION> Louisville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ky. </LOCATION>; and <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> affiliates WGAL-TV in <LOCATION> Lancaster </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pa. </LOCATION>, WYFF-TV in <LOCATION> Greenville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> S.C. </LOCATION> and WXII-TV in <LOCATION> Winston-Salem </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C </LOCATION>. The company also operates radio stations <ORGANIZATION> KTAR-AM </ORGANIZATION> and KKLT-FM in <LOCATION> Phoenix </LOCATION>. Pulitzer publishes the <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Post-Dispatch </LOCATION>, The <ORGANIZATION> Arizona </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGA